    "biography": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Dreyfus, the Shape-Walker — Level 5 Elite</strong></p><p><em>Humanoid (Shape-Walker), Medium</em></p><p>Stamina 64 | Speed 7 | Size M | Stability 2</p><p>Dreyfus appears as a grey-pale man with gold unblinking eyes, skin the colour of old ivory. But something is <em>wrong</em> with him. The edges of him flicker, like a candle in a draft. His shifting is less clean than it was — less sure. He carries the specific marks of his fight with the party in Beat 9.</p><hr><h3>Main Attacks</h3><p><strong>Talon Strike</strong> (Melee, Agility): +4 vs Agility; 9 damage. Target is Slowed (save ends).</p><p><strong>Void Pulse</strong> (Ranged 8, Presence): +3 vs Intuition; 7 damage. Target has a bane on their next test or attack roll.</p><hr><h3>Triggered Actions (costs 1 Villain Power)</h3><p><strong>Shift Form</strong> (triggered at start of turn): Dreyfus transforms into a new form. Each form has a different secondary attack:</p><ul><li><strong>Dire Wolf Form:</strong> Pack Lunge — Melee, +4 vs Might; 11 damage, target Prone.</li><li><strong>Raven Form:</strong> Wyrd-Shriek — Close Burst 2, +3 vs Intuition; 5 damage, all targets Dazed until end of next turn. (Speed 10 while in Raven form; flying.)</li><li><strong>Shadow Form:</strong> Drain Warmth — Ranged touch, +3 vs Presence; 8 cold damage, target loses 1 Recovery.</li></ul><hr><h3>Features</h3><p><strong>Flickering Body:</strong> When Dreyfus takes 10+ damage from a single hit, he immediately teleports 3 squares as a free triggered action.</p><p><strong>Wyrd-Read:</strong> Dreyfus cannot be surprised. He knows what skills each hero has used so far in the campaign and uses this knowledge tactically.</p><p><strong>Shape Collapse:</strong> When reduced to 0 Stamina, Dreyfus does not die. He collapses into a pool of shadow and is incapacitated. He cannot reform. He is finished — not destroyed, but ended as an agent.</p>",
      "director": "<p><strong>TACTICAL GUIDANCE:</strong></p><ul><li>This fight should take ~2 rounds if the party plays efficiently.</li><li>Dreyfus is dangerous (Elite) but exhausted in ways that show.</li><li><strong>Round 1:</strong> Fights with precision and cruelty. Uses Wyrd-Read knowledge to target each hero's confidence. Shifts forms to scatter positioning.</li><li><strong>Round 2:</strong> Villain Power depleted. Returns to human form. Faster, more direct — precision gone, replaced by pure violence. Most dangerous here.</li><li>At 20 Stamina: Stops shifting forms. He can't maintain the shapes. The party watches something <em>degrade</em>.</li><li>At 0 Stamina: Collapses. Flickering stops. For one moment, he looks completely human — not a shape-walker, but a person who has been doing something terrible for a very long time and has finally been stopped.</li></ul><p><strong>CALLBACK TO BEAT 9:</strong> Review what the party did to Dreyfus in Beat 9 — which PC wounded him, what weapon, where the blow landed. His degraded appearance here should carry the specific marks of that fight. If a PC drove a spear through his shoulder, his left arm doesn't shift cleanly. If they burned him, his raven form trails ash. The party should recognise their own handiwork.</p>",
      "languages": []
    },
